Greetings to Azerbaijani President 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 27 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, on May 21 sent a message of greetings to Azerbaijani President Ilham Aliyev on the occasion of the 90th anniversary of its national day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim in the message expressed the belief that the friendly and cooperative relations between the DPRK and Azerbaijan would grow stronger, wishing the president success in his work for the progress and prosperity of the country.

Sinchon Museum Visited by Endless Stream of Koreans, Overseas Compatriots and Foreigners 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 27 (KCNA) -- More than 15.4 million people have visited the Sinchon Museum in Sinchon County, South Hwanghae Province of the DPRK for the past five decades since it was opened. Among them were at least 220,000 overseas Koreans and more than 30,000 foreigners. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 During the last Korean War, the U.S. imperialists and class enemies killed more than 30,000 innocent people or a quarter of the population of Sinchon County in the most brutal way.

Sanatoriums Rebuilt 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 27 (KCNA) -- Working people of the DPRK are now enjoying medical services in the sanatoriums including the Kim Jong Suk Sanitarium at state expenses. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Sanatoriums in different parts of the country have been rebuilt on the expansion basis and a lot of modern rural houses with lodging rooms constructed around them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
A recuperation pavilion, spa treatment rooms and a general treatment center have been spruced up at the Talchon Sanatorium for Disabled Soldiers in the Jongdal Hot Spring, around which modern rural houses for recuperators have cropped up. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The Sijungho Sanatorium noted for mud treatment has been repaired and partially rebuilt. Not only the mud-treatment and physical treatment rooms but also the mess hall and bathrooms have been spruced up splendidly. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
A good many modern rural houses with lodging rooms have also taken shape for recuperators at the Hwangjin Hot Spring in the region of Mt. Chilbo, the Naegok Hot Spring in Pochon County, the Wonhung Hot Spring in Tongsin County and the Kalsan Hot Spring in Phangyo County. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
More sanatoriums are being built or rebuilt wherever hot springs or mineral springs are found. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
While expanding sanatoriums, the state has rounded off their management system.

Somokri Heron, Natural Treasure 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 27 (KCNA) -- There is a habitat of Somokri heron in Jangjin County, South Hamgyong Province of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Hundreds of herons fly to the low hill, which is called "Woegaridong", on the western shore of the Jangjin Lake on Jangjin Plateau, to lay and hatch eggs from March to October every year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Occasionally they appear in Pujon, Sinhung and Yonggwang Counties beyond the Jangjin area. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Three to seven pairs of herons perch in their nests on each tree, which look like white flowers in full bloom in green forest. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The number of Somokri herons is increasing as days go by under the protection of the government and people.

KCNA Flails Japan's Evermore Shameless Moves to Grab Tok Islet 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 27 (KCNA) -- Japan has become all the more brazen-faced in its moves to seize Tok Islet. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In February the Japanese authorities marked this islet as part of Japan's territory on the homepage of its Foreign Ministry and in May they announced their decision to designate the islet as such in "the manuals explaining the new study guidelines" for primary and middle schools. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Ministry of Education, Culture, Sports, Science and Technology justified this, openly claiming that it was to help "the younger generation who would shoulder upon themselves the future of Japan to have a correct understanding of the territory of Japan." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese authorities' intensified education in the "dominium over Tok Islet" proves that their criminal moves to teach young Japanese distorted history and instill territorial ambition into them in a bid to realize their sinister intention to grab Tok Islet have reached an extremely reckless phase in all aspects. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In recent years Japan made sure that the islet was described as "part of Japan's territory" in the textbooks for middle and high schools, openly disclosing its attempt to seize the islet, an inalienable part of Korea's territory. But it is the first time that it marked the islet as part of its territory even in the "study guidelines" and "manuals" for schools. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Tok Islet has been an inalienable part of territory of Korea since the time of its ancestors. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese authorities are sadly mistaken if they think they can grab Tok Islet by tampering with their history and unilaterally insisting on their assertion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan asserted Tok Islet's coming under the jurisdiction of Shimane Prefecture in 1905 as a "legal ground" for its "dominium over Tok Islet". But the assertion has already been proven to be hypocritical. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The fact that Tok Islet was marked as part of the territory of Korea in a textbook which was used as a teaching material for schools ranging from primary to high schools not only in Japan but in Korea and Manchuria during Japan's colonial rule over Korea was recently brought to light. There are many other data proving the injustice of Japan's "dominium over Tok Islet".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan's territorial claim to Tok Islet is a declaration of its moves for reinvasion of Korea and the revival of imperialism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The international community should heighten vigilance against Japan as it goes arrogant, seeking territorial expansion again against the backdrop of worldwide problem of natural resources, economic fluctuation and "war on terrorism." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people are greatly angered at the Japanese authorities' crafty moves to realize their ambition to grab the islet by egging the pro-Japanese sycophantic traitors in south Korea on to work harder to usher in a "new era of Japan-south Korea relations." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese authorities had better behave with discretion, bearing deep in mind that any encroachment upon the dignity and sovereignty of the Korean nation may bring unpredictable catastrophic consequences to Japan.

Japanese Reactionaries' Moves for Space Militarization Assailed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 27 (KCNA) -- A recent meeting of the House of Councillors of Japan formally adopted "a law on basic policies for the use of the space." This is aimed at legislatively allowing the military use of the space in a bid to give bigger authority to the "Self-Defense Forces" (SDF) and speed up the military expansion in the space. Minju Joson today observes this in a signed commentary. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese reactionaries are noisily advertising that the adoption of the above-said law is a measure to cope with the "threat" from someone in an effort to cover up the sinister aim sought by it, the commentary notes, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 No country in the world poses any military "threat" to Japan at present. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese reactionaries seek to realize their ambition for turning their country into a military power and their scenario for overseas expansion by hastening the space militarization under the pretext of "threat" form someone. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 To this end, they are working hard to increase the military operation capability of the SDF and build a missile shield. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Their moves for the space militarization are a link in such chain efforts. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese reactionaries are hastening the space militarization under the pretext of "defense" in an effort to boost the capability to make preemptive strikes at other countries including the DPRK and hold an unchallenged military edge. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They have long advocated the military use of the space, talking about the "right to self-defense," and frantically stepped up the preparations for it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In collusion with the U.S. they have accelerated the moves to establish a missile defense system while giving spurs to the development and launch of spy satellites. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan's moves for space militarization are wrecking world peace and stability and sparking off an arms race. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese reactionaries had better stop at once the reckless moves for the space militarization, mindful that the moves will only lead to self-destruction.

Japan Urged to Redress Its Past Crimes 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 27 (KCNA) -- Japan should liquidate its crime-woven past, to begin with, as it is a starting-point for Japan to put an end to its crime-woven history and win the trust of the international community. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Rodong Sinmun today says this in a signed commentary. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Participants in a meeting of the UN Human Rights Council held in Geneva some days ago termed the system of "comfort women" for the Imperial Japanese Army a crime against humanity and demanded that the assailants be brought to the court of justice and Japan make reparation to the victims, says the commentary. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The Japanese side, however, made poor excuses, making "apology" and expressing "regret," it notes, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There are not a few countries in the world which committed war crimes, but it is only Japan which has persistently resorted to all sorts of trickeries in a bid to evade its responsibility to liquidate its past century after century, with its crimes unredeemed. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan has already experienced a hot agony of shame while impudently behaving in a bid to become a permanent member of the UN Security Council. But Japan is attributing this distrust of the international community to its "diplomatic shortcoming" instead of finding the reason in its refusal to liquidate its past. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It can be said that Japan's foreign policy is characterized by its servility to the U.S. and diplomacy to win clout through the offer of money. The bid made by Japan to take a responsible post at the United Nations through subservience to the U.S. and money-manipulated diplomacy, putting the liquidation of its past on the shelf, cannot be construed otherwise than a move to emerge a political power and repeat the crime-woven history under the signboard of the UN. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan is employing sleight of hand to get its past crimes buried into oblivion with the passage of time, but it is nothing but a folly which can be perpetrated by the politically amaurotic persons who cannot look ahead into the future even a bit. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan should be forced to pay for such hideous abuses of human rights as sexual slavery imposed by the Japanese imperialists against Korean women, their forcible drafting of Koreans and massacres of them, etc. under any circumstances. Japan will meet a stronger protest and denunciation from the international community and stand further isolated from it if Japan continues dodging the liquidation of its past crimes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The world conscience is closely following the attitude of Japan.

Minju Joson Calls for Bringing down U.S.-S. Korea "Alliance" for Aggression
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 27 (KCNA) -- Minju Joson today calls for bringing down the U.S. and south Korean war maniacs' alliance for a war of aggression against the north in a signed commentary carried on the lapse of 40 years since the start of the south Korea-U.S. annual "defense ministers' meeting".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 During the period the name of the meeting changed into an "annual security consultative meeting" but its aggressive nature and danger remain unchanged, the commentary says, recalling the fact that the U.S. and south Korean war maniacs "discussed" the matter of stepping up the preparations for a war of aggression against the north under the signboard of "alliance" every year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What merits attention is that this alliance for a war of aggression against the north has been further tightened since the Lee Myung Bak regime emerged in south Korea, the commentary notes, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Lee is now leaving no stone unturned to "reinforce the alliance" with the U.S. No sooner had he come to power than he visited the U.S. before any other lackeys of south Korea. He put forward the so-called "value", "trust" and "peace-making" as the "three principles of alliance" while talking about the "strategic alliance in the 21st century".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The south Korean bellicose forces are now giving spurs to the preparations for a war of aggression against the north according to the outcome of Lee's junket to the U.S. He is running wild to do harm to fellow countrymen with the backing of his American master while begging the U.S. for "stronger alliance". These criminal acts of treachery committed by Lee are escalating the tension on the Korean Peninsula day by day and bringing the inter-Korean relations back to those in the past era of confrontation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. should drop its aggressive Korea policy, stop egging the south Korean puppets onto confrontation between the north and the south and withdraw its forces from south Korea. Otherwise, it will suffer such disgrace as being driven out of south Korea by the mounting nationwide anti-U.S. struggle. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Lee group would be well advised to ponder over the consequences being entailed by his sycophancy toward the U.S. and its moves for confrontation with fellow countrymen and behave with discretion.

Reckless Racket of Military Confrontation under Fire
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 27 (KCNA) -- The anti-reunification bellicose forces are bound to meet a stern judgment of history as they persistently kick up a racket of military confrontation with the DPRK while giving priority to the cooperation with the aggressive foreign forces and going against the implementation of the October 4 declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Rodong Sinmun today observes this in a signed article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  The Lee Myung Bak regime in south Korea is hell-bent on stoking confrontation with the fellow countrymen and straining tension in frantic cooperation with the foreign forces in their moves to provoke a war against the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Lee group's provocative introduction of up-to-date war hardware in the wake of its ridiculous remarks calling for a "preemptive attack on the DPRK" clearly shows that its theory of "preemptive attack" is being put into practice. A particular mention should be made of the recent visit paid by traitor Lee Myung Bak to his U.S. master and the fact that he begged it to "stop the reduction" of the U.S. imperialist forces of aggression in south Korea and raise south Korea's status in purchasing weapons. This has brought into bolder relief his true colors as traitor and warhawk hell-bent on aggravating the military tension on the Korean Peninsula and launching a war against the DPRK at any cost in military collusion with the outsiders. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  It is a precondition for implementing the October 4 declaration to eliminate all remnants spawn by the military confrontation and ensure peace. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  However, the Lee group is denying the above-said precondition and insisting on the illegal and bogus "northern limit line", the leftover of the Korean war of aggression ignited by the U.S. imperialists and the inter-Korean confrontation era.  And on this basis it is making ceaseless military provocations in the West Sea, threatening peace and aggravating the situation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  The treacherous group's reckless racket of military confrontation is a revelation of its hostility toward the DPRK and a product of its deep-seated wild ambition to invade it. This is, in essence, an outrageous challenge and the negation of the June 15 joint declaration and the October 4 declaration, programme for putting the June 15 joint declaration into practice. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  The south Korean authorities should admit and respect the June 15 joint declaration and the October 4 declaration and stop at once the military confrontation racket against the fellow countrymen in order to remove the danger of a war and achieve the development of inter-Korean relations and peace and prosperity on the Korean Peninsula at present.

Actions against Import of American Beef Unabated in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 27 (KCNA) -- A large-scale candlelight action against the import of American beef was staged in Chonggye Plaza in Seoul on May 24 under the theme "Let People judge mad cow, mad policy and mad government." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was participated in by at least 25,000 members of civic and public organizations grouping people of different social standings, citizens and students. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speakers at a candlelight rally held before other events accused the present "government" of working hard to impose the misfortune resulting from the mad cow disease upon the people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Traitor Lee will not be able to escape a stern judgement of people should he open the market to American beef siding with the U.S. government and stock-breeding enterprises, they warned. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then its participants staged a candlelight demonstration towards the "Chongwadae." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Their action continued till the morning of May 25. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  On May 23 the Federation of Student Councils of the Herbal Medical Universities of south Korea held a rally in the above-said plaza in protest against the import of American beef. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Earlier, the Federation of Student Council of Pharmaceutical Universities of south Korea, the Federation of Councils for Farmers' Health of south Korea and other organizations held a press conference at which they demanded the total nullification of the negotiations on the import of beef whose security is not proved and renegotiations on it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Youth and Students Solidarity for Implementing the June 15 Joint Declaration in a statement issued on May 23 condemned the U.S. ambassador in Seoul for his interference in the internal affairs of south Korea as evidenced by his act of threatening over phone a representative of an opposition party of south Korea who opposed the import of the beef and accused the Lee Myung Bak regime of its sycophancy toward the U.S.

Security Authorities' Suppression of Patriotic Student under Fire
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 27 (KCNA) -- The south Korean Federation of University Student Councils issued a statement on May 22 denouncing the security authorities' suppression of a pro-reunification patriotic student. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement referred to the fact that on May 21 the "Security Investigation Group" (SIG) unreasonably arrested Paek Hyong Jin, chairman of the General Students Council of Chosun University for 2004, on the charge of violation of the "National Security Law".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that the rash acts of the pro-U.S. lackeys who are not able to understand the trend of the times have already gone beyond the danger line, they called for repealing the NSL, immediately releasing all prisoners of conscience and dissolving the SIG at once.

South Korea-U.S. "Annual Security Consultative Meeting" Assailed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 27 (KCNA) -- A spokesman for the Korean National Peace Committee issued a statement on May 26 in connection with the lapse of 40 years since the U.S. and south Korea kicked off a "defence ministerial conference" under the pretext of "security." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The above-said meeting held every year since 1968 provided opportunities of hatching criminal plots to increase south Korea's total military dependence upon the U.S., perpetuate the presence of the U.S. imperialist aggressor forces in south Korea and get the south Korean puppet troops deeply involved in the moves for a war of aggression against the north and played the function as a mechanism for military consultation for aggression, the statement said, and went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Since the emergence of the Lee Myung Bak regime its military collusion with the U.S. and its moves for war have become evermore pronounced. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 No sooner had traitor Lee took the "presidential seat" than he introduced latest war hardware including nuclear-powered carriers and nuclear-powered submarines into south Korea from the U.S. and staged madcap nuclear war exercises targeted against the north such as the Key Resolve and Foal Eagle joint military maneuvers, thus driving the situation on the Korean Peninsula to a dangerous phase. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Moreover, he begged his American master to permanently keep the U.S. forces in south Korea and bolster them, talking about a "strategic alliance". He also requested the U.S. to elevate "the status of south Korea in purchasing U.S. made weapons" and went the lengths of letting it participate in the PSI and the building of a missile shield which even his predecessors hesitated to do so and contemplating knocking into shape a "triangular military alliance" involving south Korea, the U.S. and Japan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reality goes to clearly prove that the Lee group is a despicable group of servants for the U.S. in its moves for a war of aggression and war maniacs keen to bring disasters to the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 South Koreans can never be in peace nor can the nation be safe and peace and reunification on the Korean Peninsula be achievable so long as south Korea remains militarily dependent upon the U.S. and pro-U.S. flunkeys and traitors like the Lee group are allowed to ride roughshod.

Kim Jong Il inspecciona Unidad de Formacion de Suboficiales No. 1727
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 27 de mayo (ATCC) -- El Dirigente Kim Jong Il, Secretario General del Partido del Trabajo de Corea, Presidente del Comite de Defensa Nacional de la Republica Popular Democratica de Corea y Comandante Supremo del Ejercito Popular de Corea, inspecciono la Unidad de Formacion de Suboficiales No. 1727 del EPC. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Se mostro satisfecho de que la unidad realiza con eficacia la educacion de entrenamiento para que los militares novatos adiestren los reglamentos militares y los movimientos en el orden cerrado. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  En el ejercito los suboficiales inclusive el jefe de escuadra son los miembros quienes practican  directamente la vida disciplinaria y militar y son los educadores sobre los soldados, y, por esta razon, es muy importante su papel en el establecimiento de la disciplina militar, dijo y presento las  tareas que se presentan en la  labor didactica de la Unidad. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Al ver el recinto del cuartel limpio ordenado y el lugar de descanso al aire libre acondicionado dentro del bosque frondoso, el Comandante Supremo elogio la esmerada administracion de la unidad materializando estrictamente el metodo al estilo de la Guerrilla Antijaponesa. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Al recorrer la Casa de Militares, la biblioteca y otros establecimientos de cultura y educacion se entero del estado de la labor politica para los militares. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Enfatizo que deben elevar mas el grado de la educacion revolucionaria y la de clase para los militares, para hacer que todos estos vivan y luchen de manera revolucionaria manteniendo la aguda vision clasista y el firme principio revolucionario. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Recorrio el dormitorio, el comedor, el bano, el deposito de alimentos subsidiarios y otras instalaciones de intendencia prestando gran  atencion a la vida de los militares novatos. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Senalo que a fin de formar a todos estos como excelentes suboficiales es preciso mejorar incesantemente la labor docente conforme a la demanda de la realidad en desarrollo y al mismo tiempo, prestar la mayor atencion  al aseguramiento de la vida de ellos. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  El Comandante Supremo se fotografio junto a los militares de la unidad.

Kim Jong Il inspecciona subunidad de Unidad No. 836 del EPC
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 27 de mayo (ATCC) -- El Dirigente Kim Jong Il, Secretario General del Partido del Trabajo de Corea, Presidente del Comite de Defensa Nacional de la Republica Popular Democratica de Corea y Comandante Supremo del Ejercito Popular de Corea, inspecciono una subunidad adscrita a la Unidad No. 836 del EPC. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Luego de hacer conocimiento del estado de cumplimiento de la mision y del entrenamiento, el Comandante Supremo se mostro satisfecho de que todos los militares de la subunidad se forman como combatientes capaces de pelear a solas contra cien rivales y de disuadir a cualesquier enemigos muy fuertes que sean y presento las tareas para incrementar la combatividad de la subunidad. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Al enterarse en la sala de educacion de la situacion de la educacion ideologica y la vida cultural, se puso muy contento de que la subunidad realiza originalmente la labor politica conforme al sentimiento y psicologia de los militares y de que estos llevan una rica vida cultural utilizando varios equipos culturales. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Senalo que hoy dia, todas las unidades forman a sus militares como combatientes fuertes en fe prestando primordial atencion a la labor politico-ideologica y agrego que la prioridad a la idea es el remedio omnipotente propio del EPC, el metodo de construccion del ejercito a nuestro estilo y la bandera de victorias que siempre debemos levantar en alto. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Al divisar el recinto del cuartel y el bosque copioso acondicionado en los alrededores, elogio el patriotismo de los uniformados senalando que los arboles plantados hace mas de 10 anos han formado este frondoso bosque. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Subrayo que cuando los militares posean el patriotismo socialista, pueden amar apasionadamente el socialismo coreano sintiendose muy orgullosos del mismo y luchar tenazmente por defender de la agresion de los enemigos la patria socialista y las conquistas de la revolucion y anadio que ellos deben desplegar con mas vigor el movimiento por adornar mejor sus puestos. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Acto seguido, el Comandante Supremo recorrio las instalaciones de intendencia atendiendo cordialmente la vida de los militares y se fotografio junto a estos.
